parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PPS sensor can cause the passenger airbag to malfunction, leading to increased risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the passenger airbag off/service airbag warning message appears on the instrument panel
the airbag warning light remains on all the time
and the airbag may not deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for the recall repair can leave vehicles without functioning airbags, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the passenger airbag off/service airbag warning message appears on the instrument panel
and the dealer is unable to repair the vehicle due to unavailable parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate recall notification and repair process can leave vehicles without functioning airbags, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the passenger airbag off/service airbag warning message appears on the instrument panel
and the dealer or manufacturer is unable to provide a repair or a timeline for the repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes on cold start can cause accidents or near-misses, especially when backing out of a driveway or parking lot.
symptoms: The brake pedal is hard to press
the brakes do not engage
or the vehicle does not stop when the brake pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can cause accidents or rear-end collisions, especially if the driver behind the vehicle is not aware of the stopped vehicle.
symptoms: The brake lights do not illuminate when the brake pedal is pressed
or they turn off when the pedal is released.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes after hard braking can cause accidents or loss of control, especially on the highway.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brakes do not function properly
or the vehicle starts to roll again after coming to a complete stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move on an inclined surface, potentially leading to accidents or damage.
symptoms: The parking brake does not prevent the vehicle from rolling when parked on an inclined surface.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: "Service Airbag" message on the dashboard
passenger airbag light remains off even when a person is sitting in the passenger seat
airbag readiness light on the instrument panel cluster is on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to a loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: Key stuck in the ignition
unable to remove the key from the ignition
vehicle fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety-critical systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Tire pressure monitoring system failure
remote entry system failure
brake system failure
instrument panel cluster malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness can cause a fire, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Melting or ignition of the wiring harness for the A/C fan.
